    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Prints on paper from impressions of a reverse design created on a printing plate, usually copper, into which the design has been punched or struck directly with an engraving tool such as a smith's punch.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
